    dc:creator "Grenier, Marie; Ruiz, Cesar; Lage, Anaira; Perez, Thierry" ;
    dc:date "2020" ;
    dc:title "New cave-dwelling Plakina (Plakinidae, Homoscleromorpha, Porifera) from Martinique Island (French Antilles)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3629046>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3629048>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3629050>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3629052> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3629046>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. External morphology and color variation of Plakina doudou sp. nov. A) in situ photo showing Plakina doudou sp. nov. (1) living in syntopy with Plakina arletensis (2) and Tetralophophora mesoamericana (3). B) Focus on in situ specimens of Plakina doudou sp. nov. C) Same specimen after fixation in alcohol." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3629046/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3629048>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Photos taken using light (A, B) and scanning electron (C-I) microscopy of Plakina doudou sp. nov. skeleton. A) transversal section of the skeleton. B) Focus on the skeleton, showing the surface, exhalant canal, embryo and basal cavity. C) Diods. D) Triod. E) Calthrop. F) Monolophose triods. G) Monolophose calthrops. H) Dilophose calthrops. I) Trilophose calthrops. bc: basal cavity; ec: exhalant canal; em: embryo; s: surface." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3629048/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3629050>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. General organization of the tissue of Plakina doudou sp. nov. A) Semi-thin section showing two cinctoblastula embryos. B–D) Choanosome. E) Cinctoblastula embryo. F) Close-up of the cinctoblastula embryo. F) Transmission electron micrograph of the embryo. bc: basal cavity; bm: basement membrane; cav: central cavity; cc: choanocyte chamber; Ch: choanocyte; ciC: ciliated cells; cil: cilia; ec: exhalant canal; em: embryo; endo: endopinacoderm; exo: exopinacoderm; Fo: follicular cells; M: mesohyl; N: nucleus; NI: unidentified bodies. Oo: oocyte; Pi: flagellated endopinacocyte; sp: hole left by spicule; V: vitellus." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3629050/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3629052>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Transmission electron micrographs: A) Choanocyte chamber (cc). B) Focus on the limit between two choanocyte chambers. C) Apopylar cell (Ap). D) Exopinacocyte. E) Endopinacocyte. F) Symbiotic bacteria (b). Ch: choanocyte; ec: exhalant canal; fl: flagellum; in: inclusions; M: mesohyl; N: nucleus; Pi: pinacocyte; sp: hole left by spicule." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3629052/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

